{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/e7y2fm","slide":1,"text":"Open with the one-liner: Swift turns spoken natural language into native Mac actions.\nImmediately say what makes it different from simply rebuilding Siri: flexible intent, context, memory, chaining, and recoverable execution.\nBe careful: Siri is faster and more deeply integrated. Swift explores a different axis: agentic reasoning and transparent execution."}
