{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/w3m94fu1","slide":7,"text":"Done = Gemini stops calling tools and returns normal text. Five iterations is a safety cap.","textPreview":"Done = Gemini stops calling tools and returns normal text. Five iterations is a safety cap.","textChars":91,"textLines":1,"bbox":[128,610,1000,32]}
{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/7wyunb","slide":7,"text":"Be explicit: Gemini decides it is done when it returns text instead of another function call.\nThe max of 5 is a guardrail against infinite loops. Normal voice commands take 1 to 3 calls.\nThis is where cross-domain chaining comes from. It was not possible in the old one-route architecture."}
